message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with medical image analysis using semantic segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of automated adaptations based on dataset properties, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper focuses on medical applications, which could place it under the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a U-Net architecture, which is a popular neural network architecture used in medical image analysis, placing it under the neural networks (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
